label: Cyst in tounge or muscle
description: Abnormal boils in animal tounge or muscle.

label: Brain cyst
description: Abnormal fluid-filled sac in the brain.

label: Tongue vesicles
description: a small fluid-filled bladder, sac, cyst, or vacuole within the tongue

label: Brain haemorrhages
description: A brain hemorrhage is a type of stroke.

label: Meningitis
description: Meningitis is an inflammation of the meninges. The meninges are the three membranes that cover the brain and spinal cord.

label: Encephalitis
description: Encephalitis is an acute inflammation of the brain.

label: Hydrocephalus
description: Hydrocephalus is the buildup of fluid in the cavities (ventricles) deep within the brain.

label: Cerebellar hypoplasia
description: Cerebellar hypoplasia is a disorder in which the cerebellum is not completely mature at birth.

label: Alopecia
description: alopecia refers to a loss of hair from part of the head or body.

label: Diamond shaped lesions
description: The diamond-shaped lesions are characteristic of Erysipelas; the causative agent is Erysipelotrix rhusiopathiae.

label: Pus or abscess or pyaemia in skin
description: Skin abscesses are warm, painful, pus-filled pockets of infection below the skin surface that may occur on any body surface.

label: Muscle Cyst
description: A cyst is a closed sac-like structure that is not a normal part of the tissue where it is located

label: Myositis
description: Myositis means inflammation of the muscles that you use to move your body.

label: Muscle Necrosis
description: Abnormal cell death involving muscle fibers usually associated with break in, or absence of, muscle surface fiber membrane and resulting in irreversible damage to muscle fibers.

label: Pleura thickening
description: Pleura thickening, also known as diffuse pleura thickening (DPT), is a lung disease in which extensive scarring thickens the lining of the lungs (the pleura).

label: Abscess or Milky spot on lung
